Item - Class in utils
 
Item(String, String, String, int) - Constructor for class utils.Item
This represents a single item object.
Each item should have a name, description, unit cost (Amount a single unit of the item would cost) and quantity (The total unit to be added to an invoice)
Item(JSONObject) - Constructor for class utils.Item
This represents a single item object.
This constructor expects the item object to be formed as a JSONObject with the object containing fields:
item
description
unit_cost
quantity
whose values must all be String
Each item should have a name, description, unit cost (Amount a single unit of the item would cost) and quantity (The total unit to be added to an invoice)
